    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2011 BMW M3 Coupe featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8 and a tactile 6-speed manual gearbox. This driver-focused example delivers 414 horsepower with a linear power band peaking at its 8,400 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a Variable M Differential Lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution across the rear axle. Recent mechanical attention includes proactive replacement of the throttle actuators and a cooling system refresh to maintain thermal efficiency during spirited driving. The chassis retains its composure via M-specific aluminum suspension components and Electronic Damper Control (EDC). While the paintwork displays honest road patina, the individual throttle bodies and high-pressure VANOS system function flawlessly, offering the razor-sharp throttle response this platform is celebrated for. A mechanically sound specimen ready for the B-roads.",
